# EternalArchive - API Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and add at least ONE AI API key

# Supabase Configuration (Optional - for data persistence)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url_here
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# ============================================
# AI API Keys - Choose ONE or MORE
# ============================================
# The app will automatically detect and use whichever API key you provide.
# Priority order: Gemini > OpenAI > Anthropic

# Option 1: Google Gemini (FREE - Recommended for beginners)
# ✓ Completely FREE with generous limits
# ✓ No credit card required
# ✓ Great for personal projects
# Get your key from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# Option 2: OpenAI (Paid - Popular choice)
# ✓ GPT-3.5-turbo and GPT-4 models
# ✓ High quality responses
# ✓ Pay per use
# Get your key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Option 3: Anthropic Claude (Paid - Advanced AI)
# ✓ Claude 3 models (Haiku, Sonnet, Opus)
# ✓ Long context windows
# ✓ Excellent reasoning
# Get your key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here

# ============================================
# Instructions:
# ============================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Choose your preferred AI provider and get an API key
# 3. Replace the placeholder with your actual API key
# 4. Restart your development server

# ============================================
# Important Notes:
# ============================================
# - You only need ONE API key to use all tools
# - Keep your API keys secret and never commit them to version control
# - The .env file is already in .gitignore for your protection
# - All tools support file uploads (PDF, TXT, DOCX, Images, CSV)
# - See API_SETUP.md for detailed setup instructions
